  <!-- What Are Wired Open Ear Headphones -->
  <section class="section-bone">
    <h2>What Are Wired Open Ear Headphones?</h2>
    <p><strong>Wired open ear headphones</strong> let you listen to audio without blocking your ear canal. Unlike traditional wired earphones that sit deep inside your ears, open ear wired headphones rest outside, keeping your ears open to the world around you.</p>
    <p>They use a direct wired connection instead of Bluetooth, delivering stable, zero-lag audio without the need for charging. This design allows you to enjoy music, calls, gaming, or work audio while remaining aware of traffic, conversations, and important sounds.</p>
    <p>NG EarSafe’s wired open ear headphones are built for users who value <strong>safety, comfort, and reliability</strong> over gimmicks.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- How Wired Open Ear Headphones Work -->
  <section class="section-bone">
    <h2>How Wired Open Ear Headphones Work</h2>
    <p>Wired open ear headphones use <strong>air conduction</strong> to deliver sound naturally through the air instead of forcing it into the ear canal.</p>

    <p><strong>Here’s how it works:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Audio travels from your phone, laptop, or tablet through a <strong>Type-C wired connection</strong>, ensuring consistent signal strength.</li>
      <li>Speakers positioned close to your ears project sound toward the ear canal without sealing it.</li>
      <li>Your eardrum vibrates naturally, transmitting sound through the middle ear bones to the inner ear.</li>
      <li>Your brain processes the sound while your ears remain open to external noise.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>This open design reduces pressure and feels far more natural and comfortable for long hours compared to traditional in-ear wired earphones.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Choose Wired Over Wireless -->
